==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Betel
<hw>Be"tel</hw> <pr>(b⟦emac⟧"t'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg., fr.
Tamil <ets>ve⟦tsdot⟧⟦tsdot⟧ilei</ets>, prop. meaning, a mere
leaf.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species of pepper (<spn>Piper
betle</spn>), the leaves of which are chewed, with the areca or betel
nut and a little shell lime, by the inhabitants of the East Indies. It
is a woody climber with ovate many-nerved leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Betelguese</ent>⟦br⟧
